
allocPSA Installation Guide 

1) System Requirements 
      MySQL >= 4 (although it _may_ work on 3.23) (Use /usr/sbin/mysqld -V for version)
      PHP   >= 4.3.0 (Try writing a php script with <?php phpinfo();?> in it to determine version)
      Ensure PHP register_globals enabled (/etc/php.ini) Ps: sorry
      Ensure PHP memory_limit >= 64 meg (/etc/php.ini)
      Determine PHP include_path (/etc/php.ini)

2) Put the source code in a directory called alloc in the webserver document root 

3) Fill in the values in /webroot/alloc/util/install.cfg

4) Run installer script /webroot/alloc/util/install.sh

5) Remove the file /webroot/alloc/util/install.cfg


